data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and its fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` ŌĆö now takes `Func<>`, not `Expression<Func<>>`

Your manual expression-tree building **won't compile** anymore. Replace it with a simple lambda:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The new overload accepts a plain `Func`, so conditionals work naturally ŌĆö no more `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call`.

---

### 2. Complex type columns ŌĆö names are now **uniquified** and **nested paths changed**

Two sub-changes:

- **Duplicate names get a suffix**: `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` no longer silently share one column ŌĆö the second gets `Street1`.
- **Nested complex types use full path**: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City` instead of just `BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix** ŌĆö pin explicit column names to preserve your existing schema:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street")); // keep shared column
});

// For nested complex types, pin the old name:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

If you **don't** pin names, EF will generate a migration that renames columns ŌĆö potentially breaking existing data access.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` ŌĆö new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method on the interface gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging). Your class won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ŌåÉ new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
